Anyhow, the scenario I had a question about is this:  In a group in DL, our puller was rooted before getting close to where we were camped.  He started getting adds, and his health was dropping.  Our cleric was hesitant to go out, but finally followed the group to save the puller.  Long story short, puller died, adds killed another group member and almost killed two others.  <br>
<br>
So I guess what I'm asking is:  if it was your call as the cleric in that group, would you have let the puller die and rez them later?  Or would you have had the group go out and try to save the puller?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dastante>Dastante</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I love Nycah!</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/17/02 11:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm55.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Live and Let Die</span><hr size=1> If i felt like the grp could kill the mobs then yes, if there was like gore, or like 20 mobs on him no. BUT if the whole grp was going out and you guys had to convince him to go too then that cleric is a biznitch. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.imfanatic.com/whatdrinkareyou.php">discover your ALcoHoLiC personality!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
